<h4>Inhalt</h4>
<div class='textile'><p>Hanno Ehrlicher:<br />
Introduction [1–10]</p>
<p>Mechthild Albert:<br />
Visual media in the Spanish avant-garde magazine <em>La Gaceta Literaria</em> (1927–1932) – between popular traditions and modern mass-culture [11–27]</p>
<p>Torben Jelsbak:<br />
Across the Great Divide. Popular Culture in the Danish Magazine <em>Kritisk Revy</em> (1926–29) [28–41]</p>
<p>Céline Mansanti:<br />
Popular Culture in the 1920s and 1930s: A Response to America&#8217;s Cultural Identity Crisis [42–47]</p>
<p>Nanette Rißler-Pipka:<br />
The paradoxes of <em>Arte Joven</em>: high and low culture before the rise of the avant-gardes [48–64]</p>
<p>Geraldine Rogers:<br />
Strife for &#8216;the popular&#8217;: <em>Claridad</em> against <em>avant-garde</em> writers in <em>Crítica</em> (Argentina, 1926–1927) [65–80]</p></div>
